    del:madeBy <https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_383> ;
    del:text """SpoÅ¡tovani, Izrael uporablja stradanje kot vojno sredstvo. To je vojni zloÄin. Evropska unija in mednarodna skupnost morata ukrepati!
Ali bomo Å¡e naprej gledali stran in dovoljevali nadaljevanje napadov na Gazo kot na Zahodnem bregu. In to medtem ko na eni strani Trump sanja o rivieri, Izrael na novo riÅ¡e zemljevide, Palestinci Å¡e naprej brezupno umirajo.

Vse napore moramo usmeriti k dosegu dogovora druge faze, ki vkljuÄuje trajno premirje kot tudi izpustitev vseh talcev. Evropska unija pa mora odloÄno podpreti in aktivno pristopiti k arabskemu naÄrt za obnovo Gaze. RaÄun za obnovo pa moramo izstaviti Izraelu, ki je odgovoren za skoraj popolno uniÄenje Gaze, ter tistim drÅ¾avam, ki so Izraelu ves Äas vojne Å¡e naprej dostavljale oroÅ¾je. Hvala""" .

<https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_554> a del:Contribution ;
    del:identifier "contribution_554" ;
    del:madeBy <https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_384> ;
    del:text """What were Israel's options? Do nothing? Accept any demand made by the terrorists while the hostages were still being held? No country in the world would tolerate this! The EU did not negotiate with ISIS, nor did the US negotiate with Al-Qaeda!
Just as the EU sees peace negotiations between Russia and Ukraine as dangerous and invalid without security guarantees for Ukraine, it should analyse the situation between Israel and Gaza in the same manner, as long as the hostages are not released. If not, let us admit that we are applying double standards in EU institutions.
If we truly want peace, we should start by standing with those fighting against terrorism, not by legitimizing those who practice it - including here, in Europe, in Brussels, Strasbourg, Paris, and many other places.
Which of our children will be the terroristsâ next victim?""" .

