<https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_312> a del:Contribution ;
    del:follows <https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_311>,
        <https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_312> ;
    del:identifier "contribution_312" ;
    del:madeBy <https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_227> ;
    del:text """Imaginons un scÃ©nario: aprÃ¨s avoir conditionnÃ© le maintien de la protection amÃ©ricaine Ã  lâaugmentation des budgets de dÃ©fense, DonaldÂ Trump annonce demain une condition supplÃ©mentaire: le rÃ©armement de lâEurope doit se faire auprÃ¨s de lâindustrie militaire amÃ©ricaine. Ce sera le moment de vÃ©ritÃ© pour lâEurope, le moment oÃ¹ elle sera confrontÃ©e Ã  un choix existentiel: notre destin commun doit-il rester entre les mains du locataire de la Maison-Blanche, ou bien les nations europÃ©ennes sont-elles capables de retrouver confiance en elles, de croire en leur gÃ©nie, dâexploiter leur potentiel immense et de sâaffirmer sur la scÃ¨ne internationale comme une union dâÃtats libres, capables de dÃ©cider et dâagir selon ses propres intÃ©rÃªts?
Chers collÃ¨gues, disons-le tout haut: nous ne voulons ni dâune Europe russe, ni dâune Europe rendue barbare par lâislamisme, mais pas non plus dâune Europe amÃ©ricaine. Ce que nous devons rechercher et bÃ¢tir, câest lâEurope europÃ©enne.""" ;
    del:timestamp "2025-03-11T17:46:54"^^xsd:dateTime .

<https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_313> a del:Contribution ;
    del:follows <https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_312>,
        <https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_313> ;
    del:identifier "contribution_313" ;
    del:madeBy <https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_228> ;
    del:text """Despite everything we see happening all around us, we must recognise this white paper for what it is â an opportunity to shape our own future for the next generations on our own terms with our own tools. It is time to be bold in ensuring that we work towards a total defence strategy, one that combines military and civilian assets to ensure that we are no longer exposed to hostile powers to our east. One that demonstrates our commitments to our allies. One that does everything in our power to invest our political, economic, and military capital into securing our citizens.
Restoring deterrence is our primary objective. Our enemies must know and see that war against Europe and our allies is hopeless, and to do so requires us to undertake a strategic audit of European military forces and civilian assets to ensure that we outpower our enemies. The next years are a key opportunity for us to turn Europe from security consumer to security provider. We have all the tools we need to achieve this. We only need to maintain our political will.""" ;
    del:timestamp "2025-03-11T17:48:33"^^xsd:dateTime .

<https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_314> a del:Contribution ;
    del:follows <https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_313>,
        <https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_314> ;
    del:identifier "contribution_314" ;
    del:madeBy <https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_229> ;
    del:text """Câest peu, car cela repose presque exclusivement sur une dÃ©marche volontaire des Ãtats membres. Or, si beaucoup ont dÃ©jÃ  augmentÃ© leurs dÃ©penses de dÃ©fense, certains restent obstinÃ©ment Ã  la traÃ®ne. Câest peu, car rien ne dit que lâon rÃ©soudra nos principales faiblesses, celles qui rÃ©sultent de la fragmentation de nos industries de dÃ©fense et celles qui sont le fruit dâun paradoxe toxique: nos industries exportent en prioritÃ© hors de lâUnion europÃ©enne, et la plupart de nos Ãtats achÃ¨tent essentiellement hors dâEurope. Nous ne pouvons plus nous le permettre et nous devons absolument assumer une prÃ©fÃ©rence europÃ©enne marquÃ©e âÂ enfin!
Le plan dâUrsulaÂ vonÂ derÂ Leyen arrive aprÃ¨s des dÃ©cennies dâindolence. Surtout, il ne dit pas clairement comment nous allons massivement aider lâUkraine; massivement, parce que notre sÃ©curitÃ© en dÃ©pend; massivement, parce que nous sommes de plus en plus seuls Ã  le faire. Saluons donc le Conseil de jeudi dernier, mais soyons lucides: ce nâest quâune premiÃ¨re Ã©tape. DÃ©fendre les EuropÃ©ens est une ardente obligation, qui va nÃ©cessiter des efforts et, parfois, des sacrifices. PrÃ©server la paix en Europe est Ã  ce prix.""" ;
    del:timestamp "2025-03-11T17:50:13"^^xsd:dateTime .

<https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_315> a del:Contribution ;
    del:follows <https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_314>,
        <https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_315> ;
    del:identifier "contribution_315" ;
    del:madeBy <https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_230> ;
    del:text """Integrate our 27 little armies to fight as one. As President Zelenskyy said, the time has come for the armed forces of Europe to be created. So let's take the first concrete steps today. Make NATO's command and control European so we can operate as one. Jointly procure strategic enablers so we can fight effectively. Create permanent multinational units so we can get 50 extra brigades.
Europe is a peace project, but how can we be strong enough to defend it? The answer to that existential question is simple and consists of three things: Unite! Unite! Unite!
Let's not wait for war to unite us. Let's unite to prevent war. And to my Dutch colleagues in the national parliament who just voted against the REARM plans from Ms von der Leyen, I say you're making a massive mistake.""" ;
    del:timestamp "2025-03-11T17:52:23"^^xsd:dateTime .

<https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_316> a del:Contribution ;
    del:follows <https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_315>,
        <https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_316> ;
    del:identifier "contribution_316" ;
    del:madeBy <https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_231> ;
    del:text """Disons les choses, cependant: nous dÃ©pensons dÃ©jÃ  aujourdâhui de deux Ã  troisÂ fois plus que la Russie pour la guerre. Selon la presse allemande, nous avons actuellement quatreÂ fois plus de navires de guerre que la Russie, troisÂ fois plus de chars de combat et dâartillerie et deuxÂ fois plus dâavions de chasse, tandis que la Russie nâarrive heureusement pas Ã  conquÃ©rir mÃªme un quart de lâUkraine. Avant que les Russes ne dÃ©boulent sur la Grand-Place de Bruxelles, il faudra du temps! Si vous ne voulez pas lâentendre, ce nâest pas grave. Ce sont les faits, mais vous prÃ©fÃ©rez lâidÃ©ologie.
ArrÃªtez votre cinÃ©ma: tous ceux qui veulent plus dâarmes et plus de soldats, vous allez y envoyer vos enfants Ã  vous? Câest ce que vous allez faire? Non, ce seront encore les enfants de la classe ouvriÃ¨re qui devront mourir! Eh bien, nous ne lâaccepterons pas. Nous devons coordonner plus, pas dÃ©penser plus, et investir enfin dans la diplomatie.""" ;
    del:timestamp "2025-03-11T17:54:22"^^xsd:dateTime .

<https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_317> a del:Contribution ;
    del:follows <https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_316>,
        <https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_317> ;
    del:identifier "contribution_317" ;
    del:madeBy <https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_232> ;
    del:text """Ja, wer hat uns verraten? Die Christdemokraten. Die CDU stimmt hier mit den Sozialisten, Kommunisten und mit den GrÃ¼nen, obwohl es rechts hier rechtskonservative Mehrheiten gibt. Und das ist Verrat am WÃ¤hler, mein lieber Kollege. Das will Merz in Deutschland genauso tun; da will man sogar das Grundgesetz Ã¤ndern wegen 800Â Milliarden neuer SchuldenÂ â 300Â Milliarden fÃ¼r Waffen, 500Â Milliarden, um die Infrastruktur waffenâ und panzertauglich zu machen. Sie wollen uns in den Krieg treiben. Das ist esÂ â und das vÃ¶llig illegal, denn Merz will das sogar mit dem alten, abgewÃ¤hlten Bundestag machen, weil er die Mehrheiten in dem neuen Bundestag gar nicht hat. Das ist wirklich verfassungswidrig. Es gibt da Ã¼berhaupt keine EilbedÃ¼rftigkeit.
Die Menschen wollen keine Kriegstreiberei, die Menschen wollen Frieden. Weil das so ist, mÃ¼ssen Sie hier solche Spielchen spielen wie am Vormittag mit diesen NGOs. Deswegen bauen Sie hier Russland zu einem Feind auf. Von wegen Russland will uns angreifen; das ist doch vÃ¶lliger Schwachsinn. Was will denn Russland, wenn sie uns hier besetzen? Wir haben doch gar nichts auÃer Schulden â 2,5Â Billionen Schulden. Meinen Sie, das russische Volk will das abzahlen fÃ¼r uns? Und die 800Â Milliarden obendrauf? Sicher nicht.
(Die PrÃ¤sidentin entzieht dem Redner das Wort.)""" ;
    del:timestamp "2025-03-11T17:55:42"^^xsd:dateTime .

<https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_318> a del:Contribution ;
    del:follows <https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_317>,
        <https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_318> ;
    del:identifier "contribution_318" ;
    del:madeBy <https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_1> ;
    del:text """I will ask my colleagues to remember that you have the blue-card option very soon, so you have a chance to ask questions for your colleagues. And when you don't have the blue card, please let people speak quietly. Please, colleagues. Thank you.
So now we are here where I open up for the blue-card option. We always do that after the first round of speakers on behalf of the political groups. And we ended that.""" ;
    del:timestamp "2025-03-11T17:58:00"^^xsd:dateTime .

<https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_319> a del:Contribution ;
    del:follows <https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_318>,
        <https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_319> ;
    del:identifier "contribution_319" ;
    del:madeBy <https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_233> ;
    del:text """After numerous wake-up calls we have discussed here, Europe's moment of truth has finally arrived. We're not starting from scratch. In MarchÂ 2022, the 27Â heads of state or government adopted the Strategic Compass. A year later, the Commission published the European Defence Industrial Strategy, and we also adopted ASAP and EDIRPA and agreed on the capability development priorities.
All these initiatives are slowly but surely pushing Member States to step outside their national corridors in pursuit of a genuine European Defence Union. But now we really have to make a great leap.
Therefore, dear Commissioner Kubilius, the white paper must build on these achievements, and propose regulatory and programmatic initiatives at European level, rather than confining itself to a description of threats and shared needs.
You, dear Commissioner, and the HR/VP have a chance to significantly steer this debate. I look forward to discussing the white paper thoroughly at committee level.""" ;
    del:timestamp "2025-03-11T17:59:17"^^xsd:dateTime .

<https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_320> a del:Contribution ;
    del:follows <https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_319>,
        <https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_320> ;
    del:identifier "contribution_320" ;
    del:madeBy <https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_26> ;
    del:text """The dramatic reversal, of course, by our traditional American allies further underscores the need to achieve European strategic autonomy and industrial sovereignty. It actually underscores that some dependencies that we used to regard as security guarantees may, in this changed situation, prove to be vulnerabilities instead.
A stronger focus on defence and defence industrial base is not merely expenditure. It actually provides a boost for our economic competitiveness and economic activity. But it's also important to see that this additional impetus to our economic growth be shared equitably across our Union.
It has been said that we need to spend smarter and do more together, but it is obvious it's inevitable that we also need to start spending more, both at EU level, but also in our national budgets, where, let's be honest, the bulk of our defence spending and also capability generation will continue to happen.
We must be open to considering all novel ways of financing our ambitious programmes, both public and private sources. But while it may be tempting to think that at this critical time everything except defence can be put on the backburner, this is not the case, because there are two types of challenges our democracies face, both external â of military nature â but also internal. We must not provide additional fodder for the pro-Putin illiberal sentiment.""" ;
    del:timestamp "2025-03-11T18:00:36"^^xsd:dateTime .

<https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_321> a del:Contribution ;
    del:follows <https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_320>,
        <https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_321> ;
    del:identifier "contribution_321" ;
    del:madeBy <https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_46> ;
    del:text """PerchÃ©, chi Ã¨ il nemico? E quali sarebbero gli scenari strategici? PerchÃ© se il nemico Ã¨ la Russia, la Russia spende in termini assoluti, in difesa, due volte e mezzo in meno di quanto non spenda l'Unione europea e ha un PIL piÃ¹ basso dell'Italia ed Ã¨ un nono di quello dell'Unione europea ed ha una popolazione che Ã¨ un terzo di quella dell'Unione europea ed ha una capacitÃ  industriale che Ã¨ ridicola di fronte alla capacitÃ  industriale del Vecchio continente.
Ma come: negli ultimi tre anni ci avete dipinto una Russia infognata nel Donbass e che perde di fronte a un modesto avversario come l'Ucraina e oggi ce la volete dipingere come il nemico dell'intera Unione europea? Fate pace con il cervello.
La realtÃ  Ã¨ che Bruxelles vuole ingoiare la sovranitÃ  nazionale con la scusa e il pretesto della difesa comune. Quello di cui abbiamo bisogno sono nazioni forti con eserciti....
(La Presidente toglie la parola all'oratore)""" ;
    del:timestamp "2025-03-11T18:03:10"^^xsd:dateTime .

<https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_322> a del:Contribution ;
    del:follows <https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_321>,
        <https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_322> ;
    del:identifier "contribution_322" ;
    del:madeBy <https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_234> ;
    del:text """Accanto ad alcuni che abbiamo identificato come problemi, perÃ², ce ne sono altri, di scenari: oltre a quello Russia-Ucraina, c'Ã¨ il Medio Oriente, c'Ã¨ il Centrafrica, ci sono altri soggetti pericolosi per noi, c'Ã¨ la Cina, c'Ã¨ il ruolo della Turchia, c'Ã¨ il ruolo dell'Iran, c'Ã¨ l'islamismo che avanza.
Ecco, nel libro bianco mi aspetto che ci siano valutazioni di questo tipo, perchÃ© avremmo bisogno di un'industria della difesa, avremo bisogno di dual use, avremo bisogno di forze armate sempre piÃ¹ preparate e di nostri soldati sempre piÃ¹ sicuri, perchÃ© a loro va il nostro grazie.
E, come ha detto nella relazione di NiinistÃ¶, c'Ã¨ anche da guardare alla popolazione, che deve essere piÃ¹ preparata. E soprattutto ai giovani dobbiamo parlare, affinchÃ© possano avere piÃ¹ amor di patria e capacitÃ  di difesa.""" ;
    del:timestamp "2025-03-11T18:04:56"^^xsd:dateTime .

<https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_323> a del:Contribution ;
    del:follows <https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_322>,
        <https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_323> ;
    del:identifier "contribution_323" ;
    del:madeBy <https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_235> ;
    del:text """Die Welt brennt, und Russland bombardiert mehr denn je die Ukraine, und wir konnten uns heute Morgen noch einmal ein Bild davon machen, was sich dort alles abspieltÂ â das ist unmenschlich, das ist schrecklich, und noch schrecklicher ist es, dass so etwas ignoriert wird.
Europa stellt sich aufÂ â auch im Rahmen der NATO mÃ¼ssen wir stÃ¤rker werden: die europÃ¤ischen Staaten, die EU-Staaten, aber auch die europÃ¤ischen Staaten, die nicht in der EU sind. Und das ist die gute Nachricht: 29 von 32Â NATO-Staaten haben jetzt die Chance, auch unabhÃ¤ngiger zu werden.
Wir mÃ¼ssen aber auch wettbewerbsfÃ¤higer werden. WettbewerbsfÃ¤higer, damit wir eben auch in die Zukunft gehen kÃ¶nnen, denn das Geld, was wir heute in die Hand nehmen, brauchen wir, aber es muss am langen Ende auch wieder erwirtschaftet werden. Das, was wir in der Ukraine sehenÂ â ich komme noch einmal darauf zurÃ¼ckÂ â, zeigt ja Bilder, wie wir sie aus dem Ersten Weltkrieg kennen, aber auch die moderne, schreckliche KriegsfÃ¼hrung, und darauf mÃ¼ssen wir Antworten finden in Forschung, in Technik.
Ich bin dem neuen Kommissar fÃ¼r Verteidigung und Sicherheit sehr dankbar, dass er mit groÃem Elan an die Arbeit herangegangen ist. Und natÃ¼rlich ist das harte Arbeit, jetzt die Nationen zu Ã¼berzeugen, die einzelnen Staaten, dass sie auch Europa vertrauen kÃ¶nnen. Und das wird die Zukunft weisen, dass wir auch vertrauenswÃ¼rdig sind, dass wir das Geld, was wir in die Hand nehmen, auch sinnvoll und richtig einsetzen. Und das WeiÃbuch mussÂ â hoffe ichÂ â sehr klar und deutlich sein. Die Zeit von âlalaâ und âwir gucken malâ und âbusiness as usualâ ist vorbei.
Meine Damen und Herren, so wie ich gerade angefangen habe, sage ich Ihnen, dass die Welt brennt, und wir in Europa kÃ¶nnen den Unterschied machen als grÃ¶Ãtes Friedensprojekt der Welt.""" ;
    del:timestamp "2025-03-11T18:06:13"^^xsd:dateTime .

<https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_324> a del:Contribution ;
    del:follows <https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_323>,
        <https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_324> ;
    del:identifier "contribution_324" ;
    del:madeBy <https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_236> ;
    del:text "We must defend the rules-based international order, basing decisions on facts, treating partners with respect, and we must finally stand on our own feet. This means weapons and funding, but most crucially, it means attracting the brightest minds in science, tech and engineering. And here, dear colleagues, is the perfect match because many in the US also reject this administration's agenda â they too, are desperately looking for an alternative. So let's roll out the red carpet, launch a new blue card for a new era, a fast-track visa for skilled professionals from the US who want to work in Europe and build a future based on ethics, sustainability and fair growth. And to the scientists, engineers and innovators in the US: come to Europe. When autocrats embolden autocrats, democrats stand with democrats." ;
    del:timestamp "2025-03-11T18:08:50"^^xsd:dateTime .

<https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_325> a del:Contribution ;
    del:follows <https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_324>,
        <https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_325> ;
    del:identifier "contribution_325" ;
    del:madeBy <https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_80> ;
    del:text """Sie fÃ¶rdernÂ â das muss man sich mal vergegenwÃ¤rtigenÂ â Sie fÃ¶rdern und hegen und pflegen mehr die RÃ¼stungsindustrie als das, was Sie im Moment in der EU fÃ¼r die Kinder, fÃ¼r ihre Zukunft investieren und tun, und das ist inakzeptabel. AufrÃ¼stung wird weder Europa noch die Welt sicherer machen. Sie behaupten, damit wÃ¼rden Sie sogar die Demokratie stÃ¤rken. Im Gegenteil: Militarismus schwÃ¤cht die liberale Demokratie. Deshalb sagen wir Nein!
(Die Rednerin ist damit einverstanden, auf eine Frage nach dem Verfahren der âblauen Karteâ zu antworten.)""" ;
    del:timestamp "2025-03-11T18:10:22"^^xsd:dateTime .

