<https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_327> a del:Contribution ;
    del:follows <https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_326>,
        <https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_327> ;
    del:identifier "contribution_327" ;
    del:madeBy <https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_80> ;
    del:text "Wenn Sie uns heute erzÃ¤hlen, dass Abschreckung mit AufrÃ¼stung erreicht wird, dann sage ich Ihnen, auch im Kalten Krieg war es die Diplomatie, die uns davor beschÃ¼tzt hat, einen schlimmeren Krieg zu erleben als die AufrÃ¼stung selber. Deshalb, wirklich, wenn Sie keinen Krieg wollen, Herr Sieper, dann plÃ¤dieren Sie bitte fÃ¼r einen anderen Kurs in der EU als fÃ¼r die AufrÃ¼stung!" ;
    del:timestamp "2025-03-11T18:12:19"^^xsd:dateTime .

<https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_328> a del:Contribution ;
    del:follows <https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_327>,
        <https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_328> ;
    del:identifier "contribution_328" ;
    del:madeBy <https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_237> ;
    del:text """Attention, toutefois, ne remplacez pas une dÃ©pendance par une autre. Ce nâest pas la Commission europÃ©enne qui vous dÃ©fendra. La dÃ©fense dâune nation, câest sa survie, et la survie ne se nÃ©gocie pas entre bureaucrates, Ã  la majoritÃ© qualifiÃ©e. Ne donnez pas Ã  MmeÂ vonÂ derÂ Leyen le pouvoir dâenvoyer vos fils sur le champ de bataille. Il faut nous rÃ©armer, et on ne rÃ©arme pas une nation avec des comptes publics en faillite. Une Ã©conomie de guerre, ce nâest pas une machine Ã  jeter notre argent par les fenÃªtres au profit de pays du monde entier. Si nous voulons gagner la prochaine guerre, il nous faut dâabord gagner tout de suite la guerre contre le gaspillage, les gabegies et le dÃ©sordre budgÃ©taire.
Notre rÃ©armement doit bÃ©nÃ©ficier exclusivement Ã  notre industrie militaire. Si vous achetez amÃ©ricain, vous restez sous tutelle amÃ©ricaine âÂ câest aussi simple que cela. La France, seule puissance nuclÃ©aire du continent, dotÃ©e dâune armÃ©e exceptionnelle, a un rÃ´le historique Ã  jouer. Pour les nations qui voudraient se placer sous notre protection, il faudra contribuer et donner Ã  la France les moyens nÃ©cessaires, car la puissance exige des moyens. En revanche, notre dissuasion nuclÃ©aire ne sera jamais Ã  partager avec quiconque, car la puissance ne se partage pas, la puissance ne se dÃ©lÃ¨gue pas, et la sÃ©curitÃ© ne se sous-traite pas. Câest Ã  nous dâassumer lâeffort, ou Ã  nous de nous prÃ©parer Ã  en payer le prix.""" ;
    del:timestamp "2025-03-11T18:13:13"^^xsd:dateTime .

<https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_329> a del:Contribution ;
    del:follows <https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_328>,
        <https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_329> ;
    del:identifier "contribution_329" ;
    del:madeBy <https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_238> ;
    del:text """800Â MilliardenÂ Euro sollen nun in RÃ¼stung verausgabt werden, wÃ¤hrend unsere Wirtschaft im Koma liegt und unsere Infrastruktur kollabiert. Dabei geben die europÃ¤ischen NATO-Staaten bereits das Dreifache Russlands fÃ¼r RÃ¼stung aus. Russland beiÃt sich seit drei Jahren in 20Â % der Ukraine die ZÃ¤hne aus. Deswegen ist es vÃ¶llig illusionÃ¤r anzunehmen, dass sie morgen auf dem Grand Place oder vor dem Brandenburger Tor stÃ¼nden.
Eines ist aber richtig: Russland verfÃ¼gt Ã¼ber 5Â 000Â AtomsprengkÃ¶pfe, Frankreich Ã¼ber 290. Und die AfD fordert jetztÂ â ÃberraschungÂ â in Deutschland deutsche Atombomben. Mehr Sicherheit erfordert aber wechselseitige AbrÃ¼stungsinitiativen und eine neue europÃ¤ische Sicherheitsarchitektur. WÃ¤hrend Herr Trump uns StrafzÃ¶lle androht, hauen wir der USâRÃ¼stungsindustrie die AuftragsbÃ¼cher voll. Das ist vÃ¶llig widersinnig, und deswegen ist es Zeit, mit diesem Unsinn Schluss zu machen, bevor sich Generationen von UntersuchungsausschÃ¼ssen mit dem Filz im RÃ¼stungssektor befassen.
(Der PrÃ¤sident entzieht dem Redner das Wort.)""" ;
    del:timestamp "2025-03-11T18:15:32"^^xsd:dateTime .

<https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_330> a del:Contribution ;
    del:follows <https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_329>,
        <https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_330> ;
    del:identifier "contribution_330" ;
    del:madeBy <https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_25> ;
    del:text """If we are weak, we are a target. If we are strong, we are safe. This is the principle that needs to guide us. This is why I say invest more in defence, to keep our citizens safe and invest more in common European projects in defence.
Commissioner Kubilius, we very much welcome the work that you're doing, and we're very much looking forward to the white paper that you're going to propose. Our expectation is to see projects in there which we at European level can do better that than Member States can do alone. And then we should also find the funds, the resources, to support the projects which the European Commission puts forward. We should show to the people of Europe that spending money at European level on defence is worth it, and that it is better spent than at national level.""" ;
    del:timestamp "2025-03-11T18:17:06"^^xsd:dateTime .

<https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_331> a del:Contribution ;
    del:follows <https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_330>,
        <https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_331> ;
    del:identifier "contribution_331" ;
    del:madeBy <https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_239> ;
    del:text """Â¿Por quÃ©? Porque no podemos dar por garantizado el vÃ­nculo atlÃ¡ntico y tenemos una guerra en suelo europeo con una fuerza hostil a nuestras puertas.
Â¿CÃ³mo? Coordinando mejor nuestro gasto, creando capacidades europeas, gastando mÃ¡s europeo con una base industrial europea y gastando mÃ¡s en proporciÃ³n al reto que tenemos enfrente.
Â¿Para quÃ©? Para tener una fuerza de disuasiÃ³n suficiente como para evitar la guerra, es decir, para proteger la paz, para proteger nuestras democracias y tambiÃ©n para tener una diplomacia y ser un actor global creÃ­ble en el mundo.
Y, al mismo tiempo, no solo vale con crÃ©ditos y presupuesto nacional, necesitamos recursos y canales financieros europeos para hacerlo, para asegurar que, sobre todo, no entra en competiciÃ³n el gasto social con el gasto en defensa, algo que serÃ­a un suicidio polÃ­tico para Europa.Â Y, al mismo tiempo, diversificar nuestras alianzas tambiÃ©n en materia de seguridad en un mundo crecientemente multipolar. Eso es una Europa autÃ³noma.""" ;
    del:timestamp "2025-03-11T18:18:37"^^xsd:dateTime .

<https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_332> a del:Contribution ;
    del:follows <https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_331>,
        <https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_332> ;
    del:identifier "contribution_332" ;
    del:madeBy <https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_240> ;
    del:text """Pat tad, kad pirms trim gadiem Krievija iebruka UkrainÄ, mÅ«su lÄ«deri joprojÄm nesaprata vai negribÄja saprast, kÄdÄ situÄcijÄ mÄs esam. Tikai tagad, kad amerikÄÅi ir parÄdÄ«juÅ¡i mÅ«su vÄjumu, mÄs kaut ko cenÅ¡amies darÄ«t.
Tagad tiek paziÅots par 800 miljardiem lielu ieguldÄ«jumu Eiropas droÅ¡Ä«bÄ, bet tÄ ir tikai un vienÄ«gi iespÄja aizÅemties. Vai mÄs gribam vÄl vienu inflÄcijas vilni? Vai mÄs gribam vÄl vairÄk samazinÄt Eiropas konkurÄtspÄju? NekavÄjoÅ¡i ir pilnÄ«bÄ jÄatceÄ¼ zaÄ¼ais kurss un visa nauda jÄnovirza aizsardzÄ«bas industrijai. Ja mÄs to neizdarÄ«sim tÅ«lÄ«t, tad mÄs neizglÄbsim ne klimatu, ne droÅ¡Ä«bu.""" ;
    del:timestamp "2025-03-11T18:19:58"^^xsd:dateTime .

<https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_333> a del:Contribution ;
    del:follows <https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_332>,
        <https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_333> ;
    del:identifier "contribution_333" ;
    del:madeBy <https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_58> ;
    del:text """The war in Ukraine has highlighted the consequences of inaction and overreliance on external partners for European defence. Beyond Ukraine, Europe has increasingly become the target of hybrid attacks and disinformation campaigns, directly threatening our political and economic stability.
But, despite all possible efforts, NATO remains the cornerstone of our security. If Europe needs to step up, any European-led initiatives must complement, not duplicate, NATO's role.
In its current form, the joint resolution is concerning. Instead of strengthening Europe's security, it promotes an alternative to NATO, undermines the autonomy of Member States in defence matters and risks deepening confrontation with the United States â our most important ally.
Instead, Europe must focus on real security: replenishing stockpiles, strengthening transatlantic ties and investing in credible deterrence.""" ;
    del:timestamp "2025-03-11T18:21:06"^^xsd:dateTime .

<https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_334> a del:Contribution ;
    del:follows <https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_333>,
        <https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_334> ;
    del:identifier "contribution_334" ;
    del:madeBy <https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_78> ;
    del:text """Ten tweede, commissaris, maakt u gebruik van artikelÂ 122 van het Verdrag om het Parlement buitenspel te zetten. Van mij mag het, maar dat gaat de kwaliteit niet verbeteren. Een goed Europees defensiebeleid voer je niet in achterkamertjes.
Ten derde, commissaris, komt u volgende week met een witboek. Ik hoop dat het duidelijker en concreter is dan u vandaag bent geweest. Er moeten echt grote Europese programmaâs in staan en een routekaart voor een Europees leger. Ook dit zeg ik hier al tien jaar. U wilt de geschiedenis ingaan? Wel, commissaris, maak die routekaart voor dat Europees leger, of u mist de afspraak met de geschiedenis.""" ;
    del:timestamp "2025-03-11T18:22:28"^^xsd:dateTime .

<https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_335> a del:Contribution ;
    del:follows <https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_334>,
        <https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_335> ;
    del:identifier "contribution_335" ;
    del:madeBy <https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_241> ;
    del:text """This is not a theoretical discussion about where Europe shall head. This is a very serious discussion about how we can protect the international rules-based order, the national sovereignty of countries, and the right of countries to determine their own fate. Russia and Putin do not believe in that. They want their empire, they want their sphere of influence, and they are building a war economy that is threatening Europe, but also countries outside of the EU.
By this paper â and I urge you, Commissioner, to be very strong and ambitious â we show that Europe is united, that we can invest in defence, we can create military capabilities where Europe is united and can also act alone without the support of the United States. And that is something that negates the threat of Russia and protects democracy and peace in Europe â that is what we must achieve.""" ;
    del:timestamp "2025-03-11T18:23:53"^^xsd:dateTime .

