    del:madeBy <https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_250> ;
    del:text """Deklaracja niezachwianego wsparcia dla Ukrainy musi wyraÅ¼aÄ siÄ w konkretach. Potrzeba odwaÅ¼nych dziaÅaÅ, by to aktywa rosyjskie finansowaÅy obronÄ Ukrainy. BiaÅa ksiÄga to mapa drogowa, ktÃ³rej musimy siÄ trzymaÄ konsekwentnie, odwaÅ¼nie i hojnie. Musimy dozbroiÄ EuropÄ. Musimy zabezpieczyÄ nasze granice. MuszÄ byÄ jak tarcza. Musimy zapeÅniÄ nasze magazyny i musimy wykorzystaÄ ten czas.Â
Europe: stay the course.""" ;
    del:timestamp "2025-03-11T18:38:15"^^xsd:dateTime .

<https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_347> a del:Contribution ;
    del:follows <https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_346>,
        <https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_347> ;
    del:identifier "contribution_347" ;
    del:madeBy <https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_251> ;
    del:text """I am a committed transatlanticist, and I still refuse to believe that this is the end. I still have faith that America will be back, but I also know that Europe cannot wait for that. This is why it is good that European leaders are finally waking up. It is good to invest EURÂ 800Â billion in defence. It is good that countries like Germany are finally breaking free from self-imposed fiscal straitjackets.
But funds alone are not enough: we must anchor this investment in a broader security strategy, one that recognises that, in an era of hybrid warfare, social cohesion and resilience are just as vital for our security as tanks and drones. This white book offers the opportunity for us to do just that, to be a blueprint for a whole-of-society approach to defence. One that defends Europe, regardless of who is sitting in the White House.""" ;
    del:timestamp "2025-03-11T18:39:47"^^xsd:dateTime .

