    del:identifier "contribution_389" ;
    del:madeBy <https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_277> ;
    del:text "Avem nevoie de un mecanism european de descurajare militarÄ Èi economicÄ, capabil sÄ contracareze ameninÈÄrile externe fÄrÄ a depinde de NATO, Èi aici ar fi cÃ¢teva lucruri. Ãn primul rÃ¢nd, ar fi nevoie de o construcÈie a unei doctrine proprii, a unui scenariu de rÄspuns militar Ã®n cazul unui atac, Èi de operaÈionalizare a articolului 42 din Tratatul privind Uniunea EuropeanÄ, similar articolului 5 din NATO. Ne trebuie un scut european de apÄrare pentru atacuri cibernetice, de exemplu, dar poate Èi un scut antirachetÄ Èi, de asemenea, o definire clarÄ a momentelor Èi a circumstanÈelor Ã®n care Uniunea EuropeanÄ intervine militar, atÃ¢t Ã®n intern, cÃ¢t Èi Ã®n extern. Sunt investiÈii de inteligenÈÄ absolut necesare. De asemenea, ne-ar trebui Èi o structurÄ de guvernanÈÄ Ã®n apÄrare, pentru cÄ acum este fragmentatÄ." ;
    del:timestamp "2025-03-11T19:31:23"^^xsd:dateTime .

<https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_390> a del:Contribution ;
    del:follows <https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_389>,
        <https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_390> ;
    del:identifier "contribution_390" ;
    del:madeBy <https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_278> ;
    del:text """Europe must reclaim its own security. We are at the beginning of an important journey to develop a European army. Together we can turn our vision into reality, but this will require strong commitment from all of us.
This is not just about buying equipment. It's about coming together. We must address challenges with a united military force. We need to significantly expand our military capabilities. Yes, challenges will come, just as they did with introducing a common currency â the euro. But today, the euro is a pillar of European stability. Tomorrow we have to add a European army.""" ;
    del:timestamp "2025-03-11T19:33:04"^^xsd:dateTime .

