<https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_394> a del:Contribution ;
    del:follows <https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_393>,
        <https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_394> ;
    del:identifier "contribution_394" ;
    del:madeBy <https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_282> ;
    del:text """For too long, Ireland has overlooked security and defence. While we remain committed to military neutrality, it does not equate to vulnerability. Securing our territorial waters and airspace is crucial, and the Government is prioritising the much-needed investment in our defence forces.
That is why I support Ireland's increased ambition in terms of urgent investment in primary radar, naval expansion and air defence. These are not luxuries: they are fundamental to our national security.
At the same time, Ireland's commitment to neutrality remains steadfast. But neutrality must be fit for purpose for the 21st century. That means contributing meaningfully to European security and contributing in areas in which we have a considerable degree of experience and expertise â like peacekeeping, for example.
It's time to get off the fence and get on with defence.""" ;
    del:timestamp "2025-03-11T19:38:19"^^xsd:dateTime .

<https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_395> a del:Contribution ;
    del:follows <https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_394>,
        <https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_395> ;
    del:identifier "contribution_395" ;
    del:madeBy <https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_210> ;
    del:text """A UniÃ£o Europeia reconheceu o Ã³bvio: a Europa nÃ£o estÃ¡ pronta para se defender. A paz depende da forÃ§a, e a Europa nÃ£o tem a suficiente.Â Durante dÃ©cadas, acreditÃ¡mos num mundo sem guerra, numa ordem baseada em regras e num continente seguro, sem investimento em defesa.
A NATO continua a ser o pilar da nossa seguranÃ§a, imaginar uma defesa europeia isolada da AlianÃ§a Ã© uma fantasia perigosa.
NÃ£o precisamos de um exÃ©rcito europeu, mas de 27 forÃ§as armadas eficazes, interoperÃ¡veis, com padrÃµes comuns e capacidade de resposta coordenada. Isso significa mais harmonizaÃ§Ã£o, defesa aÃ©rea avanÃ§ada e uma indÃºstria de defesa robusta; assegurar o domÃ­nio estratÃ©gico no espaÃ§o e no ciberespaÃ§o, tudo isto sÃ£o escolhas que definirÃ£o o futuro da Europa.
Os desafios que enfrentamos nÃ£o sÃ£o teÃ³ricos, sÃ£o reais, e a HistÃ³ria nÃ£o espera por quem hesita. Precisamos de uma polÃ­tica de defesa Ã  altura do nosso tempo.""" ;
    del:timestamp "2025-03-11T19:39:53"^^xsd:dateTime .

<https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_396> a del:Contribution ;
    del:follows <https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_395>,
        <https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_396> ;
    del:identifier "contribution_396" ;
    del:madeBy <https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_283> ;
    del:text """Nâayons pas peur de faire face aux dÃ©fis auxquels nous sommes confrontÃ©s: une Russie trÃ¨s hostile; des Ãtats-Unis qui prennent leurs distances et nous divisent; une Turquie liberticide qui occupe un tiers de Chypre et soutient les djihadistes en Syrie et lâAzerbaÃ¯djan contre les chrÃ©tiens dâArmÃ©nie; un islamisme radical qui nous menace Ã  lâextÃ©rieur comme Ã  lâintÃ©rieur; enfin, une Chine de plus en plus puissante, dont nous sommes le plus dÃ©pendants Ã©conomiquement, car elle reprÃ©sente 21Â % de nos importations.
Soyons concrets: chaque pays doit accomplir cet effort de cohÃ©rence en achetant europÃ©en. En effet, des achats dâarmes Ã©trangÃ¨res peuvent nous empÃªcher de mener les actions militaires que nous aurions dÃ©cidÃ©es. Surtout, six Ãtats membres disposent de 120 Ã  4Â 000Â entreprises de dÃ©fense en mesure de rÃ©pondre Ã  nos besoins. Ces six pays doivent pouvoir vendre davantage en Europe et Ã©laborer des politiques industrielles communes. Câest Ã  ce seul prix que nous deviendrons indÃ©pendants et autonomes.""" ;
    del:timestamp "2025-03-11T19:40:59"^^xsd:dateTime .

<https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_397> a del:Contribution ;
    del:follows <https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_396>,
        <https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_397> ;
    del:identifier "contribution_397" ;
    del:madeBy <https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_284> ;
    del:text """To that, I would say common defence makes common sense, that security requires more than a Commission proposal and a Council consent, but a strong common effort to build a strong European industry, from steel to chemicals, from raw materials to weapons, and from food to space technology.
Above all else, it requires real unity, a grand political coalition of pro-Europeans crossing national and ideological lines, leaving the cultural wars behind and building consensus around universally accepted European values and interests.""" ;
    del:timestamp "2025-03-11T19:42:34"^^xsd:dateTime .

<https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_398> a del:Contribution ;
    del:follows <https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_397>,
        <https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_398> ;
    del:identifier "contribution_398" ;
    del:madeBy <https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_219> ;
    del:text "En segundo lugar, para reinterpretar correctamente la clÃ¡usula de seguridad colectiva del Tratado de la UniÃ³n Europea (artÃ­culo 42, apartado 7) lo que tenemos que hacer es especializar por valores aÃ±adidos la conjunciÃ³n de capacidades militares, innovaciÃ³n y ciberseguridad. Y la tercera lecciÃ³n es que eso no puede hacerse a costa ni del pilar europeo de derechos sociales ni de la cohesiÃ³n europea, de modo que resulta imprescindible ensayar herramientas e instrumentos de financiaciÃ³n nuevos, incluida, naturalmente, la deuda comÃºn para sustentar el esfuerzo defensivo de Europa." ;
    del:timestamp "2025-03-11T19:43:53"^^xsd:dateTime .

<https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_399> a del:Contribution ;
    del:follows <https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_398>,
        <https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_399> ;
    del:identifier "contribution_399" ;
    del:madeBy <https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_285> ;
    del:text """Und ich will ganz deutlich sagen: Wenn wir mehr Kredite auch gemeinsam in die Hand nehmen wollen, dann mÃ¼ssen wir dafÃ¼r sorgen, dass sie effizient eingesetzt werden, dass Transparenz herrscht und dass wir auch mehr gemeinsam europÃ¤ische Projekte nach vorne stellen.
Ich glaube, dass, wenn wir die Schuldenregeln aussetzen, das nicht ausreicht, sondern dass wir eine richtige Reform der Schuldenregeln auf europÃ¤ischer Ebene brauchen, um wirklich auch mehr gemeinsam zu investieren. Ich glaube, dass wir das nicht nur tun sollten fÃ¼r Waffen und RÃ¼stungenÂ â die alleine schaffen keinen Frieden und keine Sicherheit. Wir mÃ¼ssen auch in innere Sicherheit, in Cybersicherheit oder aber auch in Klimainfrastruktur investierenÂ â nur dann werden wir als EuropÃ¤ische Union gemeinsam wieder souverÃ¤ner.""" ;
    del:timestamp "2025-03-11T19:45:14"^^xsd:dateTime .

