    del:identifier "contribution_443" ;
    del:madeBy <https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_314> ;
    del:text "Die Frage, wie wir Ã¼ber unsere Zukunft sprechen, die mÃ¼ssen wir sowieso fÃ¼hren. Wir kÃ¶nnen nicht nur jedes Mal Klimakrise sagen, wenn es um eine Flut geht, sondern wir mÃ¼ssen endlich langfristig denken: Das schulden wir den BÃ¼rgerinnen und BÃ¼rgern und vor allem den jungen Menschen in Europa." ;
    del:timestamp "2025-03-11T20:38:38"^^xsd:dateTime .

<https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_444> a del:Contribution ;
    del:follows <https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_443>,
        <https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_444> ;
    del:identifier "contribution_444" ;
    del:madeBy <https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_315> ;
    del:text "Pourtant, les solutions Ã  la crise, MonsieurÂ SÃ©journÃ©, existent; mais cela implique un changement dâidÃ©ologie âÂ oui, cela va Ãªtre difficile. Il y a urgence, par exemple, Ã  planifier dÃ©mocratiquement la modernisation de lâoutil industriel et Ã  reprendre en main par la puissance publique des secteurs stratÃ©giques. Lâenjeu est simple: reconstruire une industrie europÃ©enne au service des travailleurs et des citoyens, et non des profits. Nous en sommes loin." ;
    del:timestamp "2025-03-11T20:39:26"^^xsd:dateTime .

<https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_445> a del:Contribution ;
    del:follows <https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_444>,
        <https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_445> ;
    del:identifier "contribution_445" ;
    del:madeBy <https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_316> ;
    del:text """Az infrastrukturÃ¡lis fejlesztÃ©sek hiÃ¡nya mÃ¡shol is Ã©rezteti a hatÃ¡sÃ¡t. PÃ©ldÃ¡ul 2029 elÅtt nem vÃ¡rhatÃ³ak Ãºj szÃ©lerÅmÅ±- kapacitÃ¡sok, a hÃ¡lÃ³zati csatlakozÃ¡sok szÅ±kÃ¶ssÃ©ge miatt. A magyar ipar kiszolgÃ¡ltatottsÃ¡gÃ¡t tovÃ¡bbÃ¡ nÃ¶veli az is, hogy bÃ¡r a kormÃ¡ny elhanyagolta az energiaberuhÃ¡zÃ¡sokat, most adÃ³fizetÅi pÃ©nzbÅl csÃ¡bÃ­tja be a gigÃ¡szi energiaÃ©hsÃ©gÅ± kÃ­nai akkumulÃ¡torgyÃ¡rakat Ã©s autÃ³gyÃ¡rakat. Ãgy pedig tovÃ¡bb emelkednek az Ã¡ramÃ¡rak, amelyek kÃ¶zvetlenÃ¼l a magyar vÃ¡llalkozÃ¡sok versenykÃ©pessÃ©gÃ©t is veszÃ©lyeztetik.
A magyar helyzet megmutatja, milyen kÃ¡rokat tud okozni a megfizethetÅ energiakÃ­nÃ¡lat hiÃ¡nya a versenykÃ©pessÃ©gnek. Ezzel szemben a tiszta ipari megÃ¡llapodÃ¡sban kijelÃ¶lt stratÃ©gia kivÃ¡lÃ³ alapot ad a fenntarthatÃ³ eurÃ³pai iparfejlesztÃ©snek.""" ;
    del:timestamp "2025-03-11T20:40:42"^^xsd:dateTime .

<https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_446> a del:Contribution ;
    del:follows <https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_445>,
        <https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_446> ;
    del:identifier "contribution_446" ;
    del:madeBy <https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_317> ;
    del:text """Noi, invece, dobbiamo sostenere un grande piano dell'industria pulita in Europa e diventare leader nel mercato delle tecnologie politiche e delle energie rinnovabili. Possiamo farlo. Servono semplificazioni per le imprese e riduzione del costo dell'energia, nel rispetto degli obiettivi del Green Deal e degli impegni presi con le prossime generazioni.
Semplificare deve significare raggiungere prima gli obiettivi di transizione, non derogare. L'Europa puÃ² e deve puntare su industrie con prodotti e servizi carbon free e, soprattutto, made in Europe.
La proposta Omnibus, in questo senso, rappresenta una sfida per tutti. "Il futuro ha un cuore antico" scriveva un autore italiano, Carlo Levi, e io credo che quel cuore non possa che chiamarsi Europa.""" ;
    del:timestamp "2025-03-11T20:42:26"^^xsd:dateTime .

<https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_447> a del:Contribution ;
    del:follows <https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_446>,
        <https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_447> ;
    del:identifier "contribution_447" ;
    del:madeBy <https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_318> ;
    del:text """En tres dÃ©cadas, la producciÃ³n industrial europea ha caÃ­do del 36 al 15Â % del total mundial. Â¿Y por quÃ©? Porque la UniÃ³n Europea, como ustedes saben, no ha parado de imponer mÃ¡s ideologÃ­a, mÃ¡s regulaciÃ³n, mÃ¡s costes energÃ©ticos y mÃ¡s barreras a la inversiÃ³n en su industria. Ahora dicen que necesitan 480Â 000 millones de euros para salvar lo que ustedes mismos han destruido, pero ningÃºn fondo puede compensar su obsesiÃ³n con la hiperregulaciÃ³n y una polÃ­tica energÃ©tica suicida.
Y lo mÃ¡s cÃ­nico, la verdad, es escuchar hoy aquÃ­ a socialistas y populares âque han impuesto esta agenda verde radicalâ fingir una preocupaciÃ³n por las consecuencias de sus propias polÃ­ticas. La imposiciÃ³n forzada del coche elÃ©ctrico y la prohibiciÃ³n del motor de combustiÃ³n son el mejor ejemplo de este suicidio industrial. Y, por otra parte, Â¿quÃ© sentido tiene, seÃ±or comisario, presumir de una reducciÃ³n de emisiones cuando lo que estamos haciendo realmente es exportarlas?
Si de verdad queremos reindustrializar Europa lo que necesitamos es energÃ­a barata, acceso real a materias primas y libertad para innovar sin que los burÃ³cratas de Bruselas decidan quÃ© sectores deben sobrevivir y cuÃ¡les no. De lo contrario, seÃ±or comisario, su BrÃºjula sÃ³lo servirÃ¡ para seÃ±alar el camino de salida a las pocas industrias europeas.""" ;
    del:timestamp "2025-03-11T20:43:36"^^xsd:dateTime .

<https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_448> a del:Contribution ;
    del:follows <https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_447>,
        <https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_448> ;
    del:identifier "contribution_448" ;
    del:madeBy <https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_319> ;
    del:text """Rafforzare il sistema produttivo europeo richiede un diverso livello di impegno perchÃ©, sia chiaro, ci troviamo in questa situazione soprattutto a causa delle pessime scelte compiute nella scorsa legislatura.
Serve un cambio concettuale, non soltanto semantico. NeutralitÃ  tecnologica, riforma ETS, meno burocrazia, ricerca e innovazione, reciprocitÃ  e sicurezza energetica rappresentano urgenze necessarie a preservare il tessuto imprenditoriale europeo e a dare slancio alla crescita, dimostrando che il Clean Industrial Deal non sia un Green Deal mascherato.
Vi chiediamo lungimiranza. Il nuovo contesto geopolitico impone decisioni coraggiose e, da parte nostra, c'Ã¨ la ferrea determinazione ad accompagnarvi e a sostenervi in questo percorso.
Abbiamo perÃ², al contempo, la necessitÃ  di una presa di consapevolezza da parte vostra degli errori commessi. Riteniamo cruciale che si cominci a considerare anche la dimensione sociale, perchÃ©, sottolineo decarbonizzare non puÃ² nÃ© deve significare deindustrializzazione e delocalizzare.""" ;
    del:timestamp "2025-03-11T20:45:10"^^xsd:dateTime .

<https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_449> a del:Contribution ;
    del:follows <https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_448>,
        <https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_449> ;
    del:identifier "contribution_449" ;
    del:madeBy <https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_320> ;
    del:text """Dans le mÃªme esprit, ce pacte doit aussi faire de lâEurope la cheffe de file de lâÃ©conomie circulaire âÂ entre autresÂ â dans le monde, afin de diminuer notre dÃ©pendance aux matiÃ¨res premiÃ¨res critiques. Câest pour cela que nous saluons le fait que vous ayez repris dans ce pacte le principe consistant Ã  nâacheter quâune seule fois: une fois les matÃ©riaux entrÃ©s sur notre territoire, nous devons les garder ici et ils doivent y rester. En les recyclant et en les rÃ©utilisant, nous rÃ©duisons notre dÃ©pendance, nous baissons les coÃ»ts et nous sÃ©curisons nos ressources.
GrÃ¢ce Ã  une Ã©nergie propre et Ã  une Ã©conomie circulaire, nous bÃ¢tirons une Europe plus forte et plus autonome.""" ;
    del:timestamp "2025-03-11T20:46:39"^^xsd:dateTime .

<https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_450> a del:Contribution ;
    del:follows <https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_449>,
        <https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_450> ;
    del:identifier "contribution_450" ;
    del:madeBy <https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_321> ;
    del:text """Câest plus ou moins la question que je vous avais posÃ©e lors de votre audition en octobre, Monsieur le Commissaire. Nous voici Ã  prÃ©sent avec la proposition du pacte pour une industrie propre, qui, je lâavoue, contient 36Â fois le mot circulaire ou circularitÃ©.
But where are the concrete policies and financing to build a secondary raw material market? How can we ease transport and recycling materials across EU borders? Nothing concrete. And looking at one of the industries in dire need of transition, the textile industry, what are we missing to actually scale up fibre-to-fibre recycling?
You might answer that this will come as part of the circular economy act, but we will have to wait 21Â months for that, so no real action will be taken to boost the circular economy with this industrial policy. My fear is that this is more than a mismatch in timing. This is actually a real strategic mistake.""" ;
    del:timestamp "2025-03-11T20:48:10"^^xsd:dateTime .

